sentences: Charles Isaac Williams (born July 18, 1932) is an alto saxophonist based in New York City.
He released three albums on the Mainstream label in the early 1970s.
In 1995 Hamiett Bluiett approached record producer Pierre Sprey's Mapleshade label and convinced them to record Williams first album in more than two decades.
